Description: Shoulder sherd with bottom of neck of black-figured East Greek pottery amphora, dinos or krater; interior: streaky brown on neck, reserved below; exterior: white slip; lowest part of neck glazed with added red line; frieze of short tongues bounded below by line at top of shoulder; below, parts of two figures: on left, naked male to left (front of head, right arm, both legs missing; left arm akimbo; possibly wearing a helmet or cap, or with red hair); upper part of long-nosed and -bearded male to right (unclear attire with added red dots above incised belt; possibly wearing a helmet or cap, or with red hair) arms seemingly extended; both figures are damaged.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1226)
